┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│     WIRING & CONNECTOR SPECIFICATIONS               │
└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘

HIGH CURRENT PATH (30A - Battery to Boost Module):
═════════════════════════════════════════════════════
Cable size:        10 AWG (6mm²) or thicker
Insulation:        600V rated
Connector:         XT90 or Anderson PowerPole
Length:            Keep < 1m to minimize loss
Current rating:    Minimum 40A (safety margin)

Example:
  Battery+ ─[10 AWG red]─→ [XT90 male] ─→ Boost module
  Battery- ─[10 AWG black]─→ [XT90 female] ─→ Boost module


LOW VOLTAGE SIGNAL PATHS (ACS758, V divider):
═════════════════════════════════════════════════
Cable size:        20-22 AWG (0.5-0.75mm²)
Insulation:        300V rated
Connectors:        Molex or JST (optional)
Shielding:         Keep away from high-current paths
Length:            Keep < 50cm if possible
Impedance:         Not critical (slow signals)

Example connections:
  ACS758 VOUT ─[22 AWG shielded]─→ ESP32 GPIO 34
  V divider OUT ─[22 AWG shielded]─→ ESP32 GPIO 35


OneWire (DS18B20):
═════════════════════════════════════════════════════
Cable size:        20-22 AWG (0.5-0.75mm²)
Type:              Twisted pair recommended
Insulation:        300V
Connectors:        Right-angle JST or direct solder
Maximum distance:  3m (recommended < 1m)
Termination:       4.7k pull-up on data line

Wiring:
  GND ─[22 AWG black]─→ DS18B20 pin 1
  DATA ─[22 AWG white, twisted]─→ DS18B20 pin 2
  +3.3V ─[22 AWG red]─→ DS18B20 pin 3
  [4.7k pull-up between DATA and +3.3V]


I2C (LCD Module):
═════════════════════════════════════════════════════
Cable size:        20-22 AWG (0.5-0.75mm²)
Type:              Twisted pair
Insulation:        300V
Connectors:        4-pin JST connector
Maximum distance:  1-3m (slower clock if longer)
Pull-ups:          4.7k on both SDA and SCL

Wiring:
  GND ─[22 AWG black]─→ LCD GND
  +5V ─[22 AWG red]─→ LCD VCC
  SDA ─[22 AWG white, twisted]─→ LCD SDA
  SCL ─[22 AWG yellow, twisted]─→ LCD SCL


USB Serial Debug (Optional):
═════════════════════════════════════════════════════
Cable:             Standard USB 2.0 cable (up to 5m)
Data rate:         115200 baud
Chips:             CH340 or FTDI (already on DevKit)
Driver:            Auto-detect on modern OS


CONNECTOR TYPES (Recommended):
═════════════════════════════════════════════════════

High-current (Battery side):
  ├─ XT90 (90A rated) - Compact, secure
  ├─ Anderson PP45 (45A rated) - Heavy duty
  ├─ Deans T-plug - Compact, lower cost
  └─ Banana plugs - Large 4mm type for 30A

Signal (Sensor side):
  ├─ JST PH 2.0mm - Standard, durable
  ├─ Dupont 2.54mm - Breadboard compatible
  ├─ Molex KK series - Industrial
  └─ Direct solder - Most reliable


COLOR CODING (Standard):
═════════════════════════════════════════════════════
+5V or Power:      RED
GND or Ground:     BLACK
Signal/Data:       WHITE, YELLOW, ORANGE (vary per use)
OneWire Data:      WHITE (twisted with BLACK for GND)
I2C SDA:           WHITE
I2C SCL:           YELLOW
